org.pikater.web.config

Class KnownCoreAgents

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.pikater.web.config.KnownCoreAgents
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<AgentInfo>

    public class KnownCoreAgents
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<AgentInfo>

    Web application's wrapper for core-defined agents. Agents correspond to "boxes" in experiment editor (1:1) and each KineticComponent has its own instance (it is created every time a user opens or refreshes the experiment editor in browser).

    Instances of this class are immutable. Use getFrom(AgentInfos) and getDummy() to create new.

    Author:
    SkyCrawl

      • getDummy

        public static KnownCoreAgents getDummy()

        An alternative for whenever using getFrom(AgentInfos) is not desirable.

        Returns a generated list of agents/boxes. Returned definitions may be altered, removed or added at will in this method. Restrictions:
        • The generated options and slots need to be valid.
        • Agent names should have distinct names.
        • Option and slot names (if both input or both output) MUST be distinct within a single agent.
